The paper deals with the identification of OFDM signals in wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the effects of wireless channel impairments, frequency offset, phase offset, and sampling mismatch, which are topics related to signal processing (cs.SI), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
